MILLENNIUM HI CARBON








Activated carbon biomass plant



MIAC, through its wholly owned subsidiary Millennium HI Carbon, LLC, owns an activated carbon plant located in Kawaihae, Hawaii. The plant  converts macadamia nut shells into activated carbon which has a diverse  range of industrial and consumer applications. The plant was acquired out of bankruptcy and represents over $50 million of investment by the original project developer. MIAC is proceeding with plans to upgrade the plant for commercial operation and profitability. MIAC believes this investment is an attractive opportunity to create shareholder value.





Visit Millennium Hi Carbon's Website


























 
