	Trade
	and other receivables primarily include amounts due from clients/trading members against their trading obligations such as securities
	purchased, daily mark to market settlement on commodity, equities & currency future contracts, sale of commodities etc. which
	are mainly secured by margin made available by the clients/trading members in form of cash, securities, fixed deposits or bank
	guarantees. All payments due from exchanges/clearing houses are duly received on clearing/settlement date.




	 




	Trade
	receivable also include receivables for advisory services rendered, which primarily comprises of receivables on account portfolio
	and wealth management services, mortgage and loan advisory services, real estate broking services and investment banking services.




	 




	In
	trading transactions with clients, the Company extends credit for the purchase of securities, using the securities purchased and
	/ or other securities in the clients’ accounts as collateral for such amounts advanced. These are limited by funding rules
	as prescribed by regulator and are subject to the Company’s credit review and daily monitoring procedures.




	 






