	(b)




	To
	diversify our risk, our loan policy also places concentration limits on the loans that we may offer.






	 




	The
	exposure-ceiling limit for a single borrower or business group is 15% of net owned funds (subject to regulations of RBI in India)
	of Moneywise Financial Services Private Limited, a subsidiary of the Group. This limit may be exceeded, in exceptional circumstances,
	by an additional 10% (i.e. upto 25%) with the approval of our loan committee.




	 




	The
	exposure-ceiling limit against a single security/commodity (aggregated across all borrowers) is 15% of net owned funds of Moneywise
	Financial Services Private Limited, a subsidiary of the Group. This limit may be exceeded, in exceptional circumstances, by an
	additional 5% (i.e. up to 20%) with the approval of loan committee. This exposure-ceiling limit is not applicable in the case
	of public issue financing loans provided that the exposure to a single borrower does not exceed 0.5% of net owned funds.





	 







