	4.3






	Market
	risk







	 




	The
	Group participates in trading and investing in various assets classes such as equity, debt securities, commodities, foreign currency
	and derivatives. These assets classes experience volatility due to economic growth levels, inflation, prices, interest rates,
	foreign exchange rates and other macro-economic factors. Any changes in market prices of these asset classes will affect the Group’s
	income or the value of its holdings of financial instruments.




	 




	The
	Group segregates its exposure to market risks between price risk, interest rate risk and currency risk.





	 







	Market
	risk exposure:







	 





	The
	table below sets out the allocation of assets and liabilities subject to market risk between trading and non-trading portfolios.




	 





