	(c)








	Currency
	risk








	 




	The
	Group is not significantly exposed to currency risk as there is no mismatch between the currencies in which sales of services,
	purchase of goods/services and borrowings are dominated and the respective functional currencies of Group companies. Further,
	the functional currencies of the Group companies are primarily the Indian Rupee and U.S. dollars and do not expose the group to
	significant currency risk. The Group considers the valuation changes in foreign currency derivatives it trades in as part of investment/price
	risk as those derivatives are exchange traded, managed and monitored based on exchange price and are settled in near term in Indian
	Rupees.




	 








