GO PUBLIC REPORT
If you are considering going public please 
				email us for our free report. 



Tiber Creek Corporation specializes 
				in assisting companies in Going Public in the United States. Our 
				services include going public, private placement preparation, 
				investor relations and public-company reporting. 

               
				We take you public directly. You do not need a public shell to 
				go public.
The president of 
				Tiber Creek is a securities attorney with over 30 years 
				experience involving public offerings and the going public 
				process.


We assist companies in going public on the NYSE, 
				AMEX, NASDAQ, OTCBB (Over the Counter Bulletin Board) and the 
				OTC (over the counter) Pink Sheets. There are no asset or 
				revenue requirements to go public on the OTC Bulletin Board or 
				the Pink Sheets; so, even a start-up can go public.

				Once a company does go public, the business typically has these 
				advantages:
       
       •  Increase in valuation when you go 
				public
       •  Going public ads liquidity for 
				investors
       •  Raising capital is easier as a 
				public company
       •  A public company can use its stock 
				for a variety of purposes, including 
          trading it for 
				advertising to promote its products, services, and stock 
				

				
				In addition to financial professionals, you can offer your stock 
				to the general public. This is a distinct advantage that a 
				public company has in comparison to a private company. Please be 
				aware that you must follow certain guidelines, including 
				registering the offering with the SEC, before offering your 
				stock to the investing public.
Foreign 
				companies can also be publicly traded in the US

                 
					We also help foreign private companies to become publicly 
				traded in the US. For foreign public companies we can assist 
				with dual listings or ADR’s (American Depositary Receipts).
